# Analysis of the Main Target Image

## Count & Layers:
- The structure consists of 6 blocks in total
- The structure has 4 layers from bottom to top

## Spatial Relationships:
- Bottom layer (1st layer): Two yellow rectangular blocks arranged in an L-shape
- Second layer (2nd layer): One red block with a semicircular cutout placed on top of the yellow blocks
- Third layer (3rd layer): One green horizontal rectangular block placed on top of the red block
- Top layer (4th layer): Two blue cubes placed side by side on top of the green block

# Selected Blocks from the Dictionary

Based on the analysis of the target structure, I need the following blocks from the dictionary:

1. Block #14 - Yellow horizontal rectangular block (left part of bottom layer)
2. Block #15 - Yellow vertical rectangular block (right part of bottom layer)
3. Block #3 - Red block with semicircular cutout (middle layer)
4. Block #11 - Green horizontal rectangular block (third layer)
5. Block #8 - Blue cube (left part of top layer)
6. Block #8 - Blue cube (right part of top layer) - using the same block twice

# Assembly Order

```
{
    Step1: Move block with index 14
    Step2: Move block with index 15
    Step3: Move block with index 3
    Step4: Move block with index 11
    Step5: Move block with index 8
    Step6: Move block with index 8
}
```
